observations.recommendation:
We recommended that Management instruct the:

Inventory Committee to conduct an inventory of its road network system at least once a year, prepare Report on the Physical Count of Local Road Network and submit the same to the Office of the Auditor not later than January 31 of each year;

GSO to render a Report on Local Road Network, maintain Local Road Inventory and Road Map and keep a complete Local Road Network Property Card for all roads and its components;

Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and the General Services Officer with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects; and

Municipal Accountant to make full disclosure of the total road network system shall be made in the Notes   to Financial Statements by the Municipal Accountant.

We recommend that Management instruct the: 
GSO to maintain stock cards for each type of supplies in accordance with Section 114 of MNGAS for LGUs;
Inventory Committee to conduct periodic physical inventory count of supplies and submit RPCI not later than July 31 and January 31 of each year for the first and second semesters, respectively in accordance with Section 124 of MNGAS for LGUs.

facilitate the appraisal of the road lots component to be recorded as part of the Road Network System;
direct the GSO to maintain LRNPC for all roads and its components;
instruct the GSO and Municipal Accountant to reconcile the local road inventory report and road map with the accounting records; and
direct the Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and the GSO of the complete description and cost segregation of the road networks.

We recommended that Management:
instruct the GSO-Designate to maintain Local Road Network Property Card and road map;
instruct the GSO and Municipal Accountant to reconcile the local road inventory report and road map with the accounting records;
direct the Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant of the complete description and cost segregation of the road networks;
require the Municipal Accountant do alternative procedures in determining unrecorded Road Networks like reconciling the accounting records with the roadmap. For the amount to be transferred to the accounting records, the guidelines of COA Circular 2015-008 should be observed; and
appraise the road lots components to be recorded as part of the Road Network System.
